cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.SI, cs.MM, cs.DC

The paper discusses the privacy and security implications of mobile messaging services, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The analysis of communication patterns and server architectures involves network infrastructure (cs.NI) and system architecture (cs.SI). The measurement framework developed for the analysis involves mobile computing (cs.MM) and distributed computing (cs.DC).
